summary: WINDSHIELD WASHER SPRAY NOZZLES FROZE DURING LOW TEMPERATURE CONDITIONS CAUSING SERIOUS VISIBILITY PROBLEMS ON HIGHWAY DUE TO SALT SPRAY.  EXTRA HEAVY DUTY 'RED' SOLUTION HAD BEEN USED, SUPPOSED TO BE GOOD FOR -30 DEGREES F.  IT APPEARS THAT THE POSITION OF THE SPRAY NOZZLES, AND PERHAPS THE POSITION OF THE RESERVOIR TANK DO NO BENEFIT FROM THE HEAT OF THE ENGINE OR DEFROSTERS.
